718514f-b.text:
(1)
Central Park West, at the S.W. corner of West 95th Street. Also shown (across clearance), is West 95th Street, north side, west from, but not including Central Park West, to, but not including Columbus Ave.
September 25, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
A more extensive view in both directions.
October 23, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.

718516f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 95th Street
718516f-a.text:
gNe22,
Central Park West, at and adjoining the N.W. corner of 95th Street. No. 1 West 95th Street, on the corner, and 352-355 Central Park West, adjoining it, will remain when the Scotch Presbyterian (L.1. 248( Chasel at 3 West 95th Street, together with the adjoining houses, is demolished in September to make room for a sixteen-story
apartment building.
May 31, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
